Description: Fragment of papyrus bearing three lines of a Coptic text written along the fibres (recto) and eight lines on the other side against the fibres (verso). The text on the back is written at right angles to that on the front, and is fainter. The papyrus was evidently reused.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (380816) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/380816)
